SIMPLE: ungod
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ungod
<hw>Un*god"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>god</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deprive of
divinity; to undeify.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cause to recognize no god; to deprive of a god;
to make atheistical.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungodly</ent>⟦br⟧
